'''Tarik''' (died in [[1994]]) was a baby [[Wikipedia:Black bear|black bear]] whose voice was one of the major components of [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca's]] vocals,<ref name="BTM">''[[Star Wars: Behind the Magic]]''</ref> along with that of a [[Wikipedia:cinnamon bear|cinnamon bear]] named [[Pooh]]<ref name="Travel Guide">[[Galactic Phrase Book & Travel Guide (real-life book)|''Galactic Phrase Book & Travel Guide'']]</ref> and a [[Wikipedia:Walrus|walrus]] named [[Petulia]].<ref name="Blog">{{SW|url=news/drawing-from-the-present-familiar-creatures-in-a-galaxy-far-far-away|text=Drawing from the Present: Familiar Creatures in a Galaxy Far, Far Away}}</ref> Tarik's growls also provided the primary voice of [[Lumpawaroo/Legends|Lumpawarrump]] in the [[1978]] TV movie ''[[The Star Wars Holiday Special]]''.<ref name="Bad Feeling">{{InsiderCite|106|I Have a Bad Feeling About This!}}</ref> He lived in [[Wikipedia:San Jose, California|San Jose's]] [[Wikipedia:Happy Hollow Park & Zoo|Happy Hollow Zoo]], where he was a popular attraction. According to the Associated Press, Tarik enjoyed "sleeping, eating, catching bear biscuits, and spending hot days on his back in his pool with his paws in the air." In October [[1994]], Tarik died of congestive heart failure, liver disease and cancer at the age of 16.<ref name="SWI">{{InsiderCite|24|StarNews}}</ref>

